parameters:
\n<Yuuki>To think you could actually escape after being
targeted by that mass of malice.
\n<Rui>What? Are you still planning to get in my way?

\n<Yuuki>Oh no, of course not. Whether you clear this or
not, it makes no difference to me.
\n<Yuuki>It doesn't matter to me, either way.
\n<Yuuki>Besides, there's something I want to ask you.

\n<Yuuki>Corridors where one could mistake for eternity
with no one in sight. Beyond the doors lies a
hellish space. A so-called game of one-sided
violence.

\n<Yuuki>Laying out these scenes, what kind of situation,
what kind of person do you imagine?

\n<Yuuki>Ah, yes, sorry. I don't get many chances to talk
to people... My words might not be very clear.
\n<Yuuki>Right, I'll just get to the point.

\n<Yuuki>If you manage to defeat Lord Tuberose, I have a
favor to ask of you.

\n<Yuuki>It might be a cruel request for a sheltered girl
like you.

\n<Yuuki>You must properly kill Lord Tuberose. Otherwise,
that child will surely suffer.

\n<Rui>If we leave him alive, will the demon he
contracted come out or something?

\n<Yuuki>Ahaha, something like that. What I'm worried about
is his soul being stolen by the demon he prayed
to.

\n<Yuuki>If the spell breaks, the eternal dream of training
in a lewd hell will vanish. Then I can return to
where I belong.

\n<Yuuki>If I'm going to fall into hell anyway, I want to
go at the same time as the person I love. That's
all.

\n<Rui>...You have some nerve, dragging innocent people
into this.

\n<Yuuki>Yes, of course. If you say that, I have no words
to return.

\n<Yuuki>Ahaha, really, you're a good person. If it doesn't
work out, let's be adored by Lord Tuberose
together.

\n<Yuuki>Now, just one step off that cobblestone and you're
clear.
あっつぅっ、優樹ちゃんビビる
校舎から逃げる、この扉のルールはそれだけと説明
\n<Rui>Can I ask just one last thing?

\n<Rui>Is it true that if we break the spell, that
eyeball will die?
\n<Yuuki>It's never been broken before, so I don't know.
\n<Rui>Now that you mention it, that does make sense...

\n<Yuuki>With a spell as outrageous as this one, there's no
way it would end without consequences.

\n<Yuuki>Besides, even if it's a lie, you, having been
freed, should be able to do something about it
with your power, right?

\n<Rui>I see... It's probably better to assume it's a
lie.

\n<Yuuki>Hehe, just kidding. In my opinion, there's zero
chance it's a lie.

\n<Yuuki>Well, there is a possibility that the person
themselves doesn't know. In that case, death might
be a mercy compared to what awaits.

\n<Yuuki>They don't have the guts to deceive people
outright.

\n<Yuuki>Even after becoming such a grotesque form, they're
still just a child at heart. Hehe... cute, isn't
it?
\n<Rui>Could it be that you like them?
\n<Yuuki>I do like them. Is that a problem?

\n<Rui>...That's not what I meant! What I wanted to ask
is, if the eyeball's spell is broken, will you
disappear too?

\n<Yuuki>Ah, but the people captured in this world are all
still alive, so I think they'll be freed.
\n<Rui>Alive? But he said some of them had died.

\n<Yuuki>That's a lie. Well, there are some who might as
well be dead, but honestly, I think you could heal
them.
\n<Rui>Why would they tell such a pointless lie...

\n<Yuuki>Well... it's just a guess, but maybe someone's
magic power was too strong and they panicked when
confronted?

\n<Yuuki>Despite all the careful planning, they got scared
and blurted out something random... right... isn't
that cute?

\n<Yuuki>Anyway, innocent girls are being violated and
moaning somewhere while we're having this
conversation.

\n<Rui>Yes, that's an important point. Thank you for
telling me.

\n<Yuuki>Mhm, glad to see you're motivated. Now off you go,
shoo shoo.

\n<Yuuki>...Wasn't there just one last thing you wanted to
ask?
\n<Rui>Uh... sorry, there's something on my mind.

\n<Rui>Are you by any chance one of the women captured by
the eyeball?

\n<Rui>Well, it's not that it matters... but if you can
be saved too then...
\n<Yuuki>It's clear why you don't have a boyfriend.
\n<Yuuki>In other words, you're a typical pain in the neck!

\n<Yuuki>This Yuuki might like to take care of others,
but...

\n<Yuuki>Men are different! With that attitude, you'll only
attract scumbags who are after your body!

\n<Yuuki>Remember this. A good woman isn't just cute,
that's not enough.
\n<Yuuki>You there. Come here for a second.

An eternal corridor where no one else seems to
exist. Beyond the doors lies a hellish space. A
so-called game of one-sided violence.

Laying out these scenes, what kind of situation,
what kind of person do you imagine?

A lonely boy who can't go home, standing outside
the door alone, yearning for playtime, knowing
only violence.

Yes, ah, I see, I understand. This is all just a
fantasy to protect one's own heart.

Mutual justification among sinners. The pain in
the neck is me.

Just a little bit. Yes, honestly, I can't say I
don't think about it.
this.PLLightOn("white3" , 100); //プレイヤーのライトをつける
